    "x": "Please see\nTerms of Use\nor visit\nWise Fees & Pricing\nfor the most up to date pricing information.\nWe're changing our fees for sending USD outside the US from 18 June 2025.  For new customers, the fees apply from 18 June 2025. For existing customers, new fees apply according to our customer notice period.\nRead about customer notice periods here\nNote\n, the name for your 'main account' in Wise can vary based on your location. To find the exact terminology used in your region, please check the product directly.\nFees for sending money for local USD payouts\nThe total Wise fee will vary depending on the currency you’re sending from and how you pay for your transfer, such as Wire, ACH or your Wise main account — you’ll see the total fee when you set up a transfer.\nHow USD payouts work for Hong Kong, Singapore, and Ukraine\nSending money with the local USD payment network happens through our partnerships with domestic banks. The money travels on domestic payment rails, instead of Swift, which makes your local USD payout faster, ensuring the recipient gets the exact expected amount.\nThe easiest way to see the total fee is by setting up a transfer in the Wise app. Once you’ve added your recipi"
