    "t": "How do I verify my address?",
    "c": "Managing Your Account",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2949804/how-do-i-verify-my-address",
    "x": "As a financial institution, we need to know who is using our services. It helps us combat money laundering and keep everyone’s money safe.\nThis means we sometimes need to ask for documents that prove your address. We’ll ask you to upload a high-quality photo or scan of a document. It must clearly show:\nYour full name:\nThis must match the name on your Wise account.\nYour full home address:\nThis must also match the address on your Wise account.\nDate of issue:\nUtility bills, bank statements, and council tax bills can't be older than 3 months.\nA logo or clear name of the sender:\nFor example, your bank or your utility provider.\nWhat documents can I use to verify my address?\nDocuments we accept\nA utility bill (gas, electric, or landline phone)\nA bank or credit card statement\nA council tax bill\nA vehicle registration or tax document\nA photo driving licence with your address and expiry date\nA rental agreement — it must display the address, along with your name and your landlord's name, and include both signatures, as well as the start and end dates of the tenancy\nFor students, a\nuniversity acceptance letter\nconfirming your on-campus address, issued within the last 3 months.\nOther documents "
