    "x": "When you're signing up, changing your details, or adding a recipient, we need to check your address. As a financially regulated institution, we have to make sure your address is valid and exists.\nIf our system can't find your address, you'll see an error message. Below you can see how to fix it.\nHow to fix an invalid address error\nMost of the time, this error can be fixed by double-checking the details you've entered:\nCheck your postcode and city.\nMake sure they’re in the correct, separate fields.\nEnter your full street address.\nIn the\nHome address\nfield (sometimes called\nAddress line 1\n), enter your complete street name, building number, and apartment or unit number.\nDon't mix details.\nMake sure you haven't entered your postcode or city in the\nHome address\nfield.\nCheck the country.\nMake sure you've selected the correct country. This option might be on the same page or the previous one.\nGood to know:\nIf your address doesn't have a house number, you can use a house name or another official local identifier.\nIt can help to look up your address on Google Maps to see how it's officially formatted.\nWhat if my address is correct?\nIn some countries, if we can't find your address, you'll s"
