    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2932128/how-do-i-edit-my-personal-details",
    "x": "You can edit most of your personal details right in your Wise account.\nFor your security, some details — like your name or date of birth after a transfer — can only be changed by us. If a field is greyed out, it means you'll need to\ncontact us\nto update it.\nHow to edit your details\nOn the app\nTap on your profile picture or initials in the top-left corner.\nSelect\nPersonal details\n.\nChoose the detail you want to edit\nOn the web\nClick on your name in the top-right corner.\nSelect\nPersonal details\n.\nClick on\nEdit details\n.\nCan't log in?\nIf you've changed your phone number and can't access your account, you'll need to\nuse another way to log in\nfirst.\nChanging your address\nYou can usually\nchange your address yourself in your settings\n. We may ask you to verify your new address.\nIf the address fields are greyed out, you can’t change it yourself. This often happens for security reasons, like if you've moved to a different country.\nContact us\nand we’ll help you.\nChanging your name\nFor security, you can't change your legal name yourself, but we can do it for you. Please\ncontact us\nand send a clear photo or scan of:\nL\negal document showing your name change (like a marriage certificate, name ch"
