    "id": "MA120",
    "t": "How do I update my address?",
    "c": "Managing Your Account",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/1QaC3bwTbNEHjWJydD79az/how-do-i-update-my-address",
    "x": "The process can vary depending on where you're moving to and from, as different countries have different rules. Sometimes we'll need to ask you for a document to verify your new address.\nHow to change your personal address\nOn the web/app:\nGo to your name/initials/profile picture in the top corner of your account\nGo to\nPersonal details\nSelect\nPersonal information\nScroll down and enter your physical address\nSelect\nSave\nOnce you save the changes, we’ll let you know if we need to verify it.\nLearn more about documents we accept as proof of address\nWhy can't you edit your address?\nYour address details might be greyed out if you've moved to a new country or if we need to verify your address for another reason. When this happens, you’ll need to provide a document so we can change it for you.\nDepending on where you're moving to we might also need you to confirm your tax details.\nLearn more about confirming your tax details here\nMoving to or from the US\nIf you move to or from the US, we will cancel your existing Wise cards. You can order a new card once your new address is verified.\nWhen do you need to provide a proof of address document?\nWe may ask for a document if:\nYour address has been v"
