    "x": "Here’s what you can do if you paid for goods or services with your Wise card, but had to wait longer than expected or received something different:\nContact the seller\nAs a first step it's best to contact the seller directly and try to resolve the issue. Sometimes if there are delays or something went wrong with the received goods, they’ll try to make it right for you. This is usually the easiest and fastest way to work it out.\nCollect information\nIf they aren't cooperative or cannot help you, we’ll need the following information:\nReceipt, email order, invoice or confirmation for the purchase\nDetailed description of what the purchase was for and how the goods or service wasn't delivered as expected.\nIf it was different, let us know how it was different than you expected\nIf it was late, let us know when it was supposed to be delivered and when you actually received it.\nDetailed description of what you’ve done so far, such as\nscreenshots of your attempts to contact the seller and their replies\nif you returned the goods or service, provide a confirmation return with the date you returned it.\nScreenshots and photos are always helpful for the investigation.\nFile a dispute\nLastly, once yo"
