    "id": "MA159",
    "t": "Setting transaction controls for your Wise card",
    "c": "Managing Your Account",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2x0JI2KSRqwLHeftJfVjhD/setting-transaction-controls-for-your-wise-card",
    "x": "You can manage the types of transactions allowed on your card by setting card controls. By using these, you can customise your card’s security and usage to fit your needs. You can set different controls for different cards.\nTo manage your card controls, go to the\nCards\ntab and select\nCard controls\n.\nList of controls\nCard Control\nDetails\nOnline payments\nTurning off this control will block all payments made over the internet, including online purchases and subscriptions.\nMagnetic stripe\nTurning off this control will block all payments made using the magnetic stripe on the back of your physical card. This includes in-store purchases where you swipe your card and ATM withdrawals where the terminal reads the magnetic stripe instead of the chip.\nContactless\nTurning off this control will block all payments made by tapping your physical card. This includes in-store purchases and withdrawing money from a contactless ATM.\nChip transactions\nTurning off this control will block all payments where you insert your card into a terminal and it reads the chip to authorise the payment. This includes in-store purchases and ATM withdrawals.\nMobile wallet\nTurning off this control will block all payments"
