    "x": "Note\n, t\nhe name for your 'main account' in Wise can vary based on your location. To find the exact terminology used in your region, please check the product directly.\nIf you or your business is in the US, and are looking to\nearn interest on your Wise account\n, this article covers if you’re eligible and how you can opt in.\nAm I eligible?\nIn order to opt in to our US interest program, you’ll need to meet all 3 requirements:\nHave a US Profile Address (currently unavailable if your registered address is in New York or Alaska)\nHave a valid Social Security Number (SSN) for personal customers, or an Employer Identification Number (EIN) for Business customers\nAre a US person — see\n*Disclaimer\nbelow\nWhy do you need my SSN or EIN?\nWe need to verify your SSN or EIN so that we can report your taxes to the IRS which is required by US regulations. These numbers are your Tax ID, so we need to verify it before you can start earning interest.\nLearn more about getting verified to earn interest as a US customer\nHow do I opt in?\nIf you’re eligible, here’s how you can opt in for interest:\nGo to your USD, EUR, or GBP currencies. If you don’t have these currencies already, you can\nopen a new currency\nUn"
