    "x": "You can use money in your account to make payments, convert money between currencies, or spend money with your Wise card.\nThere are a few different ways that you can add money to your account.\nPlease note — the methods on this page are for adding money to your main account within Wise, and\nnot\nfor adding money to jars or groups.\nHow do I add money in the Wise app?\nThis is also known as a top-up. You're topping up your account by adding money within the Wise app.\nTo add money:\nFrom\nHome\n, select Add Money, or select the specific currency you want to top up, then select Add.\nEnter the amount and currency that you want to add.\nChoose your preferred payment method and select Continue to payment.\nFollow the on-screen instructions to complete the payment.\nFor BRL: due to Brazilian regulations,\nIOF tax\nwill be charged if you add BRL when paying in another currency.\nHow do I send myself money directly from my bank?\nThis is also known as a third-party payment. Another way to add money to your account is to send it directly from your bank to your Wise account details via a bank transfer (direct deposit) like a third-party payment. You don’t have to set up a Wise transfer with this method. It"
