    "c": "Wise Card",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2935778/what-if-i-spend-money-in-a-currency-i-dont-have-in-my-account",
    "x": "If you’re planning on spending in a currency that you don’t have in your Wise account, don't worry — you can still spend money. Our Smart Conversion technology will automatically convert the currency for you that has the lowest conversion fee.\nLearn how to get your Wise card\nWhat is Smart Conversion and how does it work?\nWe use technology that takes money from the currency with the lowest conversion fees when you pay with your card. And if the currencies that you hold in your account have the same conversion fees, we'll use the one with the best exchange rate, so you get the most for your money.\nCheck the conversion fees between different currencies for your region here\nExample\nLet's say you’re buying something for 100 EUR. If you have 150 EUR in your account, it’s free to spend. If you don’t have EUR in your account, we’ll convert the amount from your other available currencies and charge a\nconversion fee\n.\nIf you only have 90 EUR in your account, but you also have money in two other currencies, we’ll automatically convert the money from the currency that has the lowest conversion fee. If the currencies you hold have the same conversion fee, we'll use the one with the best exchang"
