    "x": "With most Wise cards, you can receive money by using your 16-digit card number.\nIt's currently not available for Wise cards issued in Japan and Wise Multi-Currency Cards issued in the US.\nWhat currencies can I receive?\nYou can receive any of the 40+ currencies that you can hold in your Wise account. But if you receive a non-supported currency, we'll simply credit it in the default currency of your card.\nYou can't receive money from gambling or betting institutions.\nHow long will it take for the money to arrive?\nThe money should arrive in just a few seconds, but depending on the sender's bank, it might take longer.\nIf it does take longer than you expected, ask your sender to reach out to their bank for details.\nWhat are the limits for receiving to my Wise card?\nFor AUD, CAD, CHF, CZK, DKK, EUR, GBP, HKD, HUF, ILS, JPY, MXN, MYR, NOK, NZD, PLN, RON, SEK, SGD or USD:\n4,000 EUR per transaction and per day\n20,000 EUR per month\nFor any of the other\n40+ currencies\nyou can hold in your Wise account:\n300 EUR per transaction\n500 EUR per day\n1,000 EUR per month\nThe limits will be the equivalent in the currency you're receiving.\nRefunds\nRefunds will arrive in the currency your sender sends it "
