    "x": "There are three types of spending limits on a Wise Business account:\naccount limits\ncardholder limits\n(only for businesses who have added team members)\nlimits per card\nFor all limit types, you have:\na monthly limit, which refreshes on the first day of the month\na daily limit, which refreshes each day at midnight\nApply to\nSet and edited by\nMandatory or optional\nAccount limits\nThe amount you and any team members can spend and withdraw overall\nAccount owner, Team members with permission to set team members’ card spending limits\nMandatory\nCardholder limits\nThe amount each team member can spend and withdraw across all their cards\nAccount owner, Team members with permission to set team members’ card spending limits\nAccount owners — Optional        /            Other team members with permission to order cards — Mandatory\nLimits per card\nThe amount that can be spent and withdrawn on a specific card\nThe team member who owns the card\nOptional\nHow do these different spending limits work together?\nYou and your team members’ spending will always be restricted by the lowest relevant limit.\nFor example, if a team member has a 5,000 GBP cardholder limit but sets a 10,000 GBP limit on one of their"
