    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2935789/contactless-payments-arent-working-for-my-wise-card",
    "x": "Contactless is a safe and easy way to pay. But if it’s not working, here are the most common ways to fix it.\nIf contactless suddenly stops working\nFor security, we occasionally ask you to use Chip and PIN to make sure it’s still you. This can happen after you’ve made several contactless payments in a row.\n1. Make a Chip and PIN payment.\nInsert your card into the payment terminal and enter your 4-digit PIN. This reactivates contactless payments.\n2. Check your contactless setting is on.\nIf a Chip and PIN payment doesn’t help, check that contactless payments are enabled for your card in the app:\nGo to the\nCard\ntab\nTap\nManage payment methods\nMake sure\nContactless\nis turned on\n3. Check your spending limits.\nIf your payment is declined, you may have reached your daily or monthly limit for that payment type:\nGo to the\nCard\ntab\nTap\nLimits\nto see your remaining limits\nYou can increase your limits here if you need to\nLearn more about your card spending limits\nIf your transaction isn't showing in your activity\nIf a payment is declined but you don’t see the transaction in your\nWise activity\n, it usually means there was a connection issue between the shop's payment terminal and Wise.\nThis isn’t"
