    "x": "There could be a number of reasons why your Wise card transaction isn’t showing up in your activities.\nHere are some possible reasons, and what you can do.\nCountry incompatibility\nThe merchant (the service or company billing you) might not accept cards issued in a different country from where they're based. This is often the case in the US, where many businesses only accept US cards. If that's the case, you need to use a local card.\nOnline payments\nIf it was an online payment, there might have been a technical issue with the merchant. Try deleting your card details from their website,\ntroubleshooting your browser,\nand making the payment again.\nAuthorisation fail\nThe shop or business you bought from never asked Wise to authorise the payment. Try the purchase again, or contact the merchant directly to sort out the situation. Wise won't be able to influence this transaction.\nOffline terminal payments\nIf your payment was accepted, the terminal where you used your card might have been offline. This usually happens on an aeroplane or underground.\nIf you spend more money than you have on your account before the merchant captures this transaction, your account might go negative. When it ha"
