    "x": "If you’re having trouble adding your Wise card to a mobile wallet like Apple Pay or Google Pay, the problem is usually related to eligibility or a missed step in the process.\nThis guide will help you check if you're eligible and show you how to add your card correctly.\nStep 1 — Check if your card is eligible\nTo add your card to a mobile wallet, you need to have:\nA Wise card issued in a supported country\nAn\nactive\nWise card (it can't be frozen, blocked, or cancelled)\nThe latest version of the Wise app installed\nA device that supports the mobile wallet you want to use\nSupported Wallets and Countries\nCard issued in\nApple Pay\nGoogle Pay\nSamsung Pay\nFitbit Pay\nGarmin Pay\nAustralia (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️*\n✔️\n✔️\nBrazil (Personal)\n✔️\n✔️\n❌\n❌\n❌\nBrazil (Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n❌\n✔️\n✔️\nCanada (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n❌\n❌\n❌\nEEA Countries** (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\nGreece (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n❌\n❌\nGuernsey (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\nIsle of Man (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\nJapan (Personal and Business)\n❌\n❌\n✔️\n❌\n❌\nJersey (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\nMalaysia (Personal)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️*\n❌\n❌\nNew Zealand (Personal and Business)\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n✔️\n"
