    "id": "WI281",
    "t": "How Young Explorer app access works",
    "c": "Wise Card",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/498bRngHAvLNeWb5iiIrfh/how-young-explorer-app-access-works",
    "x": "Young Explorer app access is currently only for Wise account holders living in UK and Switzerland.\nWith Young Explorer, your child can see a limited view of the money you set aside for them through the Wise app.\nYou’ll need to help them get access by generating a unique QR code within your app and sharing it with them.\nIt’s really important they don’t try to register for the app without your QR code.\nOnce they have access, they’ll be able to:\nLog in using facial recognition or a passcode —\nWe’ll prompt them to set this up the first time they access the app\nSee the money you set aside for them —\nThey won’t get access to any other part of your account\nYou can\ncheck the full list of what your child can and can’t do\n— it also shows you what permissions you and any additional adults have, too.\nReady to share app access with your child?\nLog in to your app\nGo to your Young Explorer account\nTap\nGive your child app access\nWe’ll talk you through the next steps\nIt’s best if you're with your child when you give them access, so they can easily scan the QR code you generate from within your app."
