    "x": "Parents who set up a Young Explorer Account can choose how much their child can spend in a day and over a month. If you set up the account, your child’s spending will count towards your overall account limits.\nAlthough you can choose your child’s spending limits, they can’t exceed certain amounts each month. How much your child can spend in total each month depends where you live.\nDue to local regulations, if your registered address is in Australia, New Zealand or Singapore, there are limits on the amounts your child can hold in their Young Explorer Account at any one time, too.\nWhere you live\nHow much your child can spend in total each month\nHow much money your child can hold in total\nAustralia\n999 AUD\n999 AUD\nBrazil\n10,000 BRL\nNo limit\nNew Zealand\n690 NZD\n999 NZD\nSingapore\n1,600 SGD\n999 SGD\nSwitzerland\n1,000 CHF\nNo limit\nUK\n1,000 GBP\nNo limit\nThese monthly limits include both card spending and ATM usage. \n\nIf you’re a customer based in Singapore, ATM usage isn’t allowed locally or abroad."
