    "t": "I'm expecting money, but it hasn't arrived yet",
    "c": "Receiving Money",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2977937/im-expecting-money-but-it-hasnt-arrived-yet",
    "x": "If you’re waiting for a payment, don't worry. Here’s a checklist to help you find your money.\n1. Check the date\nMost transfers are processed on\nworking days\nonly.\nWeekends and holidays:\nBanks usually don't process payments on weekends or public holidays. If the money was sent on a Friday, it likely won't arrive until the next working day\nTime zones:\nIf the sender is in a different time zone, their bank might be closed even if yours is open\n2. Check your Wise account\nWe might have paused the transfer to keep your money safe while we ask for more information. We'll always email you if we do, but it's worth checking your account too.\nCheck your Activity list:\nLook for any pending tasks or notifications on your home screen\nCheck your limits:\nSome currencies have limits on how much you can receive. If a payment takes you over the limit, we may have to refund it.\nLearn more about receiving limits\nCheck your email:\nSearch your inbox and spam folder for emails from Wise. We might be asking to verify your identity or for more information about the transfer\n3. Check with the sender\nIf your account looks fine, the issue might be with the sender's transfer. Ask them to check:\nThe details:\nDid "
