    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2978029/how-long-does-it-take-to-receive-money-into-my-wise-account",
    "x": "If you're expecting a payment into your Wise account details, you'll want to know when it'll arrive. The time it takes depends on a few things:\nThe currency that was sent\nThe payment method the sender used\nWhen the payment was sent, as payments sent on weekends and holidays can cause delays\nWhen will my payment arrive?\nPayments are usually processed during working days, Monday–Friday. If a payment was sent over a weekend or a public holiday in the sending country, it should arrive on the next working day.\nHere's an overview of how long each currency typically takes.\nCurrency\nDomestic payment\nInternational  payment (Swift)\nAUD\nUsually a few minutes, sometimes up to 1 working day\nUsually 1 working day, sometimes up to 5 working days\nCAD\nUsually a few hours, sometimes up to 1 working day\nUsually 1 working day, sometimes up to 5 working days\nEUR*\nUsually a few minutes, sometimes up to 1 working day\nUsually 1 working day, sometimes up to 5 working days\nGBP*\nUsually a few minutes, sometimes up to 1 working day\nUsually 1 working day, sometimes up to 5 working days\nHUF\nInstant for payments under 10 million HUF, a few hours for payments over 10 million HUF\nUsually 1 working day, sometimes u"
