    "id": "RE297",
    "t": "What are the fees and limits for receiving money?",
    "c": "Receiving Money",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2978013/what-are-the-fees-and-limits-for-receiving-money",
    "x": "When getting paid to your Wise account, most payment types are free to receive,  and you can receive almost any amount. Read on to see exceptions.\nLearn how to get account details and what currencies you can receive\nFees\nTo check any of our current fees for receiving money, go to our\npricing page\n— just set it to your region at the top.\nSometimes, the sender’s bank may charge a fee before the payment reaches us, so reach out to the sender to check with their bank.\nDomestic fees\nReceiving domestic payments for the majority of currencies is free.\nThe only currency with any domestic receiving fees is USD for domestic wire transfers. However, ACH payments, (direct deposits) in USD are free to receive.\nLearn more about receiving using your USD account details\nSwift fees\nThere are fees to receive international (Swift) payments for all currencies. Additionally, when someone pays you by Swift, some\ncorrespondent banks might apply their own fees\non top of the payment.\nCheck\nthe pricing page\nfor the most up-to-date Swift receiving fees for your region.\nLimits\nFor most currencies, there's no limit on how much you can receive to your account. But check the relevant currency article under\nUsing"
