    "id": "RE304",
    "t": "How our account details use partner banks",
    "c": "Receiving Money",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/31JKZjRRkfpSsDd0lE3X0T/how-our-account-details-use-partner-banks",
    "x": "We work with partner banks to provide account details for some of our supported currencies.\nWorking with partner banks means that you can receive a wider range of currencies, using both domestic and\ninternational Swift\npayment methods.\nWhen you’ll see partner bank details\nWhen you want to receive money with your account details, you might need to provide the partner bank’s details to the person sending the money. Or your sender might see the partner bank’s name shown when they make the payment instead of Wise's name.\nDon’t worry — as long as you use the account details shown in your Wise account, the money will arrive safely to your account. And we always display the partner bank details clearly alongside your other account details, so you can share them all with people sending you money.\nGetting help with partner banks\nAlthough some of our account details are provided by partner banks, your account is with Wise — not the partner bank. So if you need any help, make sure you contact us first.\nLearn more about receiving money into your account details\nLearn more about the Wise account\nLearn how Wise keeps your money safe"
