    "id": "WI350",
    "t": "Why do I need to verify my business?",
    "c": "Wise Business",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2977981/why-do-i-need-to-verify-my-business",
    "x": "Verification is one of the ways we keep your business’s money safe, and\ncomply with the financial regulations\nin the countries that we operate in.\nThat’s why, when you open a business account, we may ask you for a few documents or to confirm your details on a business registry. This helps us verify who you are, that your business is currently trading, and it meets our\nacceptable use policy\n. Think of it like opening a bank account — except that with Wise you can do the whole thing online, quickly and easily.\nReady to open your business account? Read our\nguide to getting verified\n.\nWhy am I being asked to provide additional verification information when I've already been verified?\nWe know that you provide information to us when you join Wise, but sometimes we need to request up-to-date info about your identity.\nWe may ask for this to comply with regulatory requirements. If you receive an email from us about this please follow the instructions and provide the necessary information and documents to continue using your Wise account."
