    "c": "Wise Business",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2969315/how-does-wise-verify-my-business-address",
    "x": "As a financial institution, Wise needs to verify where your business operates to comply with regulations and keep everyone's money safe.\nFor all businesses, we collect two addresses:\nRegistered address\n— where your business is officially registered and the one listed on your official business registration document (for example, on your Companies House registration).\nTrading address\n— where you actually run your business day-to-day (your office, home, shop, etc.)\nThese may be the same address, but it's also perfectly acceptable for them to be different. This can also be a co-working space.\nWhat can't my trading address be?\nYour trading address must be a physical location. It can't be:\nA PO Box\nA mail forwarding or receiving service\nA virtual office\nA solicitor's or attorney's office\nA business registration agency\nHow do I add or update my business address?\nYou can usually update your business address in your Wise account. Make sure you’re currently viewing your business account.\nOn the website:\nSelect your business name in the top right corner.\nSelect\nBusiness details\n.\nUnder\nTrading addresses\n, select\nEdit\n.\nEnter your physical trading address and select\nSave\n.\nOn the app:\nTap on y"
