    "c": "Wise Business",
    "u": "https://wise.com/help/articles/2663302/how-do-i-fill-in-my-batch-template",
    "x": "First, select and\ndownload a template\n. You’ll also find a template builder guide for each one to help you fill it in.\nBatch payments are currently not available for Brazilian businesses.\nFilling in the template fields\nEach template has its own default columns. They’ll vary depending on the type and currencies you choose. The most important columns are:\nName\n— the name of your recipient, as shown on their bank account\nsourceCurrency\n— the currency you use to pay for your batch\ntargetCurrency\n— the currency your recipients will get\nAmount\n— the value amount of your transfer (numerical characters only)\namountCurrency\n— defines your payment type:\nFixed Source Payment\n— choose this to send an exact amount in the source currency. The fees will be deducted from your recipients\nFixed Target Payment\n— chose this\nto send an exact amount to your recipients in the target currency. The fees will be deducted from you, and your recipients will get the exact amount\nFor a\nsaved recipient template\n, you'll also see these mandatory fields:\nrecipientId\n— a unique reference to a pre-existing recipient in your Wise account. You can get this by downloading the\nsaved recipients template\nrecipientDetail\n—"
